http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/karnataka/%E2%80%98Protect-environment-by-planting-trees%E2%80%99/article13979737.ece

‘I had urged the State government to set up a maternity hospital in my village, Hulikal in Magadi taluk. But the authorities have not responded positively so far,” environmentalist Salumarada Thimmakka has said.She was here on Saturday to participate in the first anniversary of ‘Swachchata Abhiyan’ undertaken by the Pahare Vedike, Karwar. She planted a sapling to inaugurate the event. Ms. Thimmakka urged the people to protect the environment by planting trees as they would give shelter and shadows to pedestrians.Deputy Commissioner Ujwalkumar Ghosh, vedike president Nagaraj Naik, and Satish Sail, MLA were present.